● Logistic Regression from Scratch + sklearn: Using the Breast Cancer Wisconsin
dataset, implement Binary Logistic Regression manually using NumPy - define the
sigmoid, compute log - loss, and run gradient descent to update weights. Then train the
same model using sklearn's LogisticRegression(). Compare manually computed weights
vs sklearn coefficients side by side. Plot the decision boundary on two selected features.
Extend to multiclass classification using the Iris dataset with OvR strategy and print
.predict_proba() outputs.
